@2016 = ~In the plains of the Eastern Shaar, lived a small blacksmith of the human race whose almost dwarfish stature was not up to his soul. Although he was a skilled blacksmith, his real skill was to whistle a soulful song that could bring a seasoned man to cry like a child. Only a reclusive mage spent his time with the little person, while the others only made fun of his small size. The song of the blacksmith met only deaf ears because of their prejudices, and their cruel mockery grew into torment, and so the discouraged man found himself finally urged to leave his home for good. Before his departure he forged this weapon as a gift for his friend, who enchanted it during the manufacturing. The blade whistles a sweet tune to its wearer when it is drawn from its sheath. Shortly after the mage also left the small town in disgust, taking the sword on his travels.

STATISTICS:

